  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Access to diverse, agricultural produce and improved nutrition practices in indigenous communities</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Fundaci&#xF3;n Nuna works in the Department of La Paz, supporting rural indigenous communities to achieve improvements in sustainable agricultural production and community organisation. This project will provide small-scale farming households with training and technical accompaniment in sustainable and innovative agricultural practices aiming to increase their production and also reduce their vulnerability to the impacts of climate change. The team will also provide support to improve resilience, providing training on the transformation and sale of agricultural produce and on the extraction / gathering of seeds from current crops for future harvest cycles.  The team promote civic participation, transparency and accountability, in particular through the participation and skills of women, young people and children</narrative>
  </description>
